Dear women! Here are the announcements for the new week.

üîπWednesday, December 4, 2024
6:00 PM
Ukrainian House, ul. Zamenhofa, 1

Psychological master class with body practices.
Conducted by - psychotherapist Tetyana Moiseyeva.
Holidays, among them Christmas, which for many centuries has been a holiday of faith and hope - are already at the doorstep.
However, instead of joy in your heart, you might feel completely different emotions? Maybe you want to celebrate, but... where is that festive mood? This is normal, especially in such a difficult time.
During the workshop, we will talk about how to manage anxiety, fatigue, or perhaps guilt. We will create a cozy space for dialogue, practices of psycho-emotional self-regulation, and support.
We will also talk about how to truly allow yourself to rejoice and relax and what valuable things this can bring not only to us but also to our loved ones.
As all workshops conducted by Tetyana Moiseyeva are interactive, for your comfort, it is better to come in comfortable clothing.
Participation of children or men is not anticipated.
The expected duration of the meeting is 2 hours.
The number of places is limited.
Registration at the link:

üîπFriday, December 6, 2024
10:00 AM
Kadr Cultural Center, ul. Wincentego Rzymowskiego, 32 (Warsaw).

Workshop on self-massage of the neck and d√©colletage area with elements of exercises for good posture.
Conducted by - professional cosmetologist Tetyana Tkachenko.
The workshop will focus on massage techniques for the neck and d√©colletage area plus exercises for good posture. Such a massage combined with appropriate exercises positively affects the circulatory and lymphatic systems, enhances collagen production, increases muscle and skin tone, and contributes to the improvement of the psycho-emotional state.
For your convenience, please wear clothing with an open neck and d√©colletage, and have a rubber band or clip to tie your hair.
Attention! Professional cosmetics with vitamin C will be used at the workshop. If you have sensitive skin, you may bring your own cosmetics. Please be responsible when participating in the workshop if you are prone to allergic reactions.
Participation of children or men is not provided for.
Expected duration of the meeting - 2 hours.
Limited number of places.
Registration link:

üîπSaturday, Saturday, December 7, 2024 10:00 am Solec 38, Warsaw (landmark cafe The Cool Cat)

Pilates training. Conducted by - certified trainer, group program instructor Inna Datsenko. Pilates is one of the safest types of training, which includes a set of exercises for the whole body, developing flexibility and mobility. It is a conscious work with all muscle groups, spine and breathing. Pilates positively affects not only physical fitness but also emotional state! In pilates, all exercises are performed slowly and smoothly, without sudden movements. That is why such physical activities are suitable for participants of any age and fitness level! Please do not be late and arrive in advance at 9:45 am. For training, you need to have comfortable sportswear, sports shoes, and water, as well as a mat. Participation of children and men is not provided. Childcare option is not available! The duration of the session is 1 hour. The number of places is limited. Registration at the link:

üîπSunday, December 8, 2024
11:00 AM
Ukrainian House, ul. Zamenhofa, 1

Practical Psychological Workshop "First Dates: Psychology of Choice and Interaction"
Led by - psychologist-sexologist, consultant in transactional analysis methods and systemic family psychotherapy Yuliya Kvasnytsia.
Do you want to feel more confident on a first date and in general when choosing a partner? Not sure how to recognize "red flags" in the behavior of a potential partner? Interested in how to communicate correctly and evaluate relationship dynamics?
In the workshop, we will:
examine the key moments of a first date;
provide tools for analyzing partner's behavior;
help understand cultural differences if the partner is a foreigner;
conduct an interactive exercise in the format of "speed dating" to learn how to recognize important details in dialogue.
What will you gain? Practical techniques to work on your expectations and boundaries.
Analytical exercises for a deeper understanding of yourself and your behavior.
The opportunity to practice communication skills in a safe space.
The expected duration of the meeting is 2 hours.
Children and men are not intended to participate. Childcare option is not available.
The number of places is limited.

Gratitude for work, for friends, for every tear, for new acquaintances and support. For every minute of life. In our friendly circle, a three-meter neuro-drawing with hearts of gratitude "From Heart to Heart" was created. The common cause united and inspired all of us. So in an uplifted mood, we thanked for the opportunity to be thankful.

text_entities.TRANSLATED_TEXT: A special meeting concluded the week dedicated to the tenth anniversary of the Ukrainian Women's Club. Together with the club's founder - the head of the Ukrainian House Foundation, Myroslava Keryk, and her associates who have been building the club from the very beginning, we reminisced about how it all started. We honored the memory of an active Club member, Nadia Smuk, who, after returning to Ukraine, joined the military and died saving her comrades. It was a meeting of tender memories and personal stories, mutual congratulations and sincere thanks. Over 10 years, the Club has changed - now we gather not only on Sundays but also on weekdays. Thus, our meetings take place an average of 6 times a week. This year, the Club had over 3700 visits! The most active participants of the meetings received symbolic awards. Among the surprises - a video greeting from our friends and Club members who have already left Poland, a lottery drawing, and memorable gifts. Together, we envisioned the next 10 years of our Ukrainian Women's Club!

text_entities.TRANSLATED_TEXT: The topic of personal boundaries is broad. It concerns our personal living space, including the physical zone, emotional, intellectual, and even digital space. What do you feel in moments when your boundaries are violated? How does your body react? What emotions do you have? How to defend your boundaries? How to show respect for the boundaries of others? The intimate atmosphere of the meeting allowed women to open up and talk about personal matters. The host's comments and recommendations highlighted important and practical points. We are grateful for the comfortable space for our resourceful meetings at Dom Kultury Kadr.

text_entities.TRANSLATED_TEXT: Dear women, please pay attention to the Business Booster project - an educational-mentoring program for Ukrainian entrepreneurs in Poland. The application is open until 5.01.2025! üì£ We invite 20 Ukrainian entrepreneurs who run businesses in Poland to join the program. As part of the project, each participant will receive 20 hours of individual business mentoring with an experienced mentor. During the individual sessions, mentors will assess needs and work on the development strategy of the company in the local market. Mentoring sessions will include: Working on the company's development strategy in Poland. Assistance in analyzing the Polish market. Providing support in discussions with suppliers, partners, and clients. Assistance in contacts with government institutions. Assistance in establishing new valuable business contacts. Knowledge exchange necessary for doing business in Poland. The program will also include three online training sessions on the topics: 'Types of entrepreneurial activities in Poland, forms of taxation, obligations, and prospects of accounting in Poland' 'Small business management' 'Legal responsibility of the enterprise - practical aspects of business activity according to the legislation' The program starts on January 1, 2025, and will last for the next 4 months. Enrollment in the project occurs in two stages: Stage 1 involves filling out an application form. After completing the form, selected companies will be invited to an online interview regarding staffing for the project. Registration for the program:
More about the program:
The Business Booster project is funded by the EBRD (European Bank for Reconstruction and Development) and co-funded by the European Union. Co-organizer of the project: Empowerment Foundation.
